From d8ce5c26de6d2987df25b63578c03632fa1dddd6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
Date: Thu, 10 Apr 2025 23:26:32 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] mac80211: wifi allow CAC while operation is going on in case 
 of MLO

Commit "ff311bc11a7e: (nl80211: allow CAC only if no operation is going on)"
added logic to return -EBUSY while starting radar detection if operation is
already going on the intended interface. However, with MLO, it is possible
that interface is operating already and one of the link is starting radar
detection. Hence, same check does not apply to MLO.

Add change to not check for operation in case of MLO.

Signed-off-by: Aditya Kumar Singh <quic_adisi@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
---
 net/wireless/nl80211.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/net/wireless/nl80211.c b/net/wireless/nl80211.c
index 0e28fce..6e32453 100644
--- a/net/wireless/nl80211.c
+++ b/net/wireless/nl80211.c
@@ -10765,6 +10765,9 @@ static int nl80211_start_radar_detection(struct sk_buff *skb,
 	if (dfs_region == NL80211_DFS_UNSET)
 		return -EINVAL;
 
+	if (!wdev->valid_links && netif_carrier_ok(dev))
+		return -EBUSY;
+
 	err = nl80211_parse_chandef(rdev, info, &chandef, wdev);
 	if (err)
 		return err;
-- 
